:File:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/filemgr.handbook
File

Provides functions so you can open, create,
duplicate, print, find, and transfer files. You 
can also add your own commands to execute.

Open		Opens the selected file or 
		displays the contents of the 
		selected folder.

Open in Editor	Opens the selected file in 
		Text Editor.

Create Document	Creates a new document
		(called "NewDocument").

		NewDocument is a file in either 
		Text Editor format or the format 
		of the Default Editor you 
		specified in Edit -> Properties -> 
		Advanced Settings.

Create Folder	Creates a new folder
		(called "NewFolder").

Duplicate	Duplicates the selected file(s)
		and adds a number to the 
		file or folder name.

Print One	Prints the selected file.

Print		Displays a window in which you
		can specify print options and
		number of copies to print.

Find		Displays a window in which you
		can specify search criteria
		such as name, owner, and 
		modification date.

Information	Displays a window containing
		information about a selected file
		such as its size or type.

Remote Copy     Displays a window in which you can
                transfer files to or from a
                remote system.
 
Custom Commands Choose from a list of frequently 
		used operating system commands or
                opens a Command Tool.

Check for Floppy
		File Manager checks to see if a
		floppy disk is inserted.  If it
		is, a Floppy Disk window pops up.
		
Format Floppy	Active only for floppy disk 
		windows.  Formats the floppy disk.

Rename Floppy	Active only for floppy disk 
		windows.  Renames the floppy disk.

Comments	Sends your comments back to the
		File Manager development team.

Quit File Manager
		Really quit File Manager.  File 
		Manager will recreate your
		environment when you restart.
 
